这是一个 **SharePoint List 连接 ComboBox 的已知问题**。

**原因：** `DisplayFields` 和 `SearchFields` 属性在 ComboBox 连接 SharePoint List 时，Power Apps Studio 会忽略你手动输入的列名，自动替换成 SharePoint 内部的第一个 metadata 字段（`ComplianceAssetId`）。这不是你的操作问题，是 SharePoint List 数据源和 ComboBox 的 schema 兼容问题，Microsoft 社区有大量报告。

**最可靠的修法：** 把 `cmbPolicyEvent` 换成 **Dropdown**，并在 `OnVisible` 里用 `AddColumns` 给 `colPolicyEvents` 加一个纯文本的显示列，这样完全绕开 `DisplayFields` 的问题。

---

## 第一步 — 修改 `OnVisible` 里的 `ClearCollect`

在现有 `ClearCollect(colPolicyEvents, ...)` 后加一行 `AddColumns`，把 `EventName` 单独提取成一个干净的显示列：

```powerapps
Refresh(PolicyEvents);
Refresh(EmployeeScopes);
Refresh(Batches);
Refresh(BatchLines);

Set(
    varUserEmail,
    Lower(Trim(User().Email))
);

ClearCollect(
    colPolicyEvents,
    Sort(
        Filter(
            PolicyEvents,
            Status = "Ready" || Status = "Draft"
        ),
        ScheduledTime,
        SortOrder.Ascending
    )
);

ClearCollect(
    colPolicyEventDisplay,
    AddColumns(
        colPolicyEvents,
        DisplayLabel,
        EventName & " (" & SystemCode & ")"
    )
);

Set(
    varSelectedPolicyEventID,
    If(
        CountRows(Filter(colPolicyEvents, Status = "Ready")) > 0,
        First(Filter(colPolicyEvents, Status = "Ready")).PolicyEventID,
        If(
            CountRows(colPolicyEvents) > 0,
            First(colPolicyEvents).PolicyEventID,
            Blank()
        )
    )
);

Set(
    varSelectedSystemCode,
    LookUp(
        colPolicyEvents,
        PolicyEventID = varSelectedPolicyEventID,
        SystemCode
    )
);

Set(
    varSelectedEventLabel,
    LookUp(
        colPolicyEventDisplay,
        PolicyEventID = varSelectedPolicyEventID,
        DisplayLabel
    )
);

ClearCollect(
    colManagerScopes,
    AddColumns(
        Filter(
            EmployeeScopes,
            ManagerEmail = varUserEmail &&
            ActiveFlag = "Y" &&
            SystemCode = varSelectedSystemCode
        ),
        SelectedAction,
        "No Change"
    )
);

Set(
    varManagerName,
    If(
        CountRows(colManagerScopes) > 0,
        First(colManagerScopes).ManagerName,
        User().FullName
    )
)
```

